```java
// OLD WAY — each is 5 lines
Comparator<Product> byPrice = new Comparator<Product>() {
    @Override
    public int compare(Product a, Product b) {
        return Double.compare(a.getPrice(), b.getPrice());
    }
};
```

```java
// LAMBDA WAY — each is 1 line
Comparator<Product> byPriceAsc    = (a, b) -> Double.compare(a.getPrice(), b.getPrice());
Comparator<Product> byPriceDesc   = (a, b) -> Double.compare(b.getPrice(), a.getPrice());
Comparator<Product> byName        = (a, b) -> a.getName().compareTo(b.getName());
Comparator<Product> byCatThenPrice = (a, b) -> {
    int cat = a.getCategory().compareTo(b.getCategory());
    return cat != 0 ? cat : Double.compare(a.getPrice(), b.getPrice());
};
Comparator<Product> byFinalPrice  = (a, b) -> Double.compare(a.finalPrice(), b.finalPrice());
```

The block lambda for byCatThenPrice has two lines — requires `{...}` and explicit `return`.

